  "prompt": "How do I use WhatsApp on a PC?",
  "response": "To use WhatsApp on a PC, you have two main options:\n\n1. WhatsApp Web:\n- Open web.whatsapp.com in your browser\n- Open WhatsApp on your phone\n- Go to Settings > Linked Devices\n- Scan the QR code on the computer screen with your phone\n- You can now use WhatsApp on your PC\n\n2. WhatsApp Desktop App:\n- Download the official WhatsApp Desktop app from whatsapp.com\n- Install the app\n- Follow the same QR code scanning process as WhatsApp Web\n- The desktop app offers a slightly more integrated experience\n\nImportant notes:\n- Your phone must remain connected to the internet\n- Your phone must stay on and unlocked\n- The process is the same for both Windows and Mac computers\n- You'll need an existing WhatsApp account on your smartphone\n\nBoth methods allow you to:\n- Send and receive messages\n- Make voice and video calls\n- Share files and media\n- View status updates\n\nChoose the method that works best for your needs and device.",
